WEBVTT

00:24.000 --> 00:26.000
[shovel thudding]

00:33.000 --> 00:34.000
[man panting]

00:40.000 --> 00:42.000
[thudding continues]

00:43.000 --> 00:44.000
[water splashing]

01:17.000 --> 01:21.000
[Herschel]  In old country of Schlupsk, I am ditch digger.

01:24.000 --> 01:26.000
It is not always great.

01:50.000 --> 01:52.000
Life is difficult.

01:52.000 --> 01:54.000
But then one day,

01:54.000 --> 01:56.000
Hashem gives me a miracle.

01:56.000 --> 01:58.000
[indistinct chatter]

02:02.000 --> 02:05.000
[Herschel]  Her name is Sarah.

02:05.000 --> 02:07.000
She is strong

02:07.000 --> 02:11.000
and she has all her teeth, top and bottom.

02:11.000 --> 02:13.000
I decide at once to woo her.

02:13.000 --> 02:15.000
[speaking foreign language]

02:17.000 --> 02:19.000
[speaking Yiddish]

02:24.000 --> 02:26.000
[Herschel]  Wooing fails,

02:26.000 --> 02:28.000
but I am determined to win her.

02:32.000 --> 02:35.000
Every day, I dig twice the ditch.

03:10.000 --> 03:13.000
It is greatest summer of my life.

03:13.000 --> 03:15.000
We have so much in common.

03:15.000 --> 03:18.000
Her favorite color black. My favorite color black.

03:18.000 --> 03:20.000
Her parents murdered by Cossacks.

03:20.000 --> 03:23.000
My parents murdered by Cossacks.

03:23.000 --> 03:26.000
I notice nice little thing about her.

03:26.000 --> 03:28.000
She always sneeze same way.

03:29.000 --> 03:30.000
Four time.

03:32.000 --> 03:34.000
Is adorable.

03:37.000 --> 03:40.000
Sometimes, when we want to be alone,

03:40.000 --> 03:42.000
we go to very special bog.

03:42.000 --> 03:45.000
We tell each other all our hopes and dreams.

03:46.000 --> 03:47.000
[Sarah speaking foreign language]

04:01.000 --> 04:02.000
[chuckles]

04:21.000 --> 04:22.000
Oh.

04:30.000 --> 04:31.000
[both chuckling]

04:34.000 --> 04:35.000
[sighs]

05:03.000 --> 05:06.000
[Herschel]  We have wedding in front of whole town.

05:08.000 --> 05:10.000
Hashem blesses us.

05:10.000 --> 05:11.000
[shouts in foreign language]

05:11.000 --> 05:12.000
[Herschel]  For a bit.

05:17.000 --> 05:19.000
We are attacked by Cossacks.

05:19.000 --> 05:21.000
Bloodthirsty, Jew-hungry,

05:21.000 --> 05:24.000
Russian maniacs drunk from vodka.

05:24.000 --> 05:25.000
Jew!

05:25.000 --> 05:28.000
-[sword swishing] -[indistinct shouting]

05:28.000 --> 05:32.000
[Herschel]  The Cossacks destroy our whole world.

05:33.000 --> 05:35.000
But...

05:36.000 --> 05:38.000
we are the Greenbaums.

05:38.000 --> 05:40.000
We are strong.

05:40.000 --> 05:43.000
And together there is no stopping us.

05:43.000 --> 05:48.000
We keep fighting till we have American dream.

05:48.000 --> 05:51.000
[man] All right, let's get these

05:48.000 --> 05:51.000
dumb Polacks outta here.

05:51.000 --> 05:52.000
[child screams]

05:52.000 --> 05:56.000
[Herschel] Compared to Cossacks,

05:52.000 --> 05:56.000
Americans very kind.

05:56.000 --> 05:59.000
[man] All right. This way, you filthy Jews. Let's go.

05:59.000 --> 06:02.000
[Herschel]  I find good job in pickle factory.

06:02.000 --> 06:04.000
A good Jewish business.

06:04.000 --> 06:07.000
The foreman will not let me mix salt.

06:07.000 --> 06:09.000
Or sort cucumber.

06:09.000 --> 06:12.000
But he says I can chase rats with club

06:12.000 --> 06:16.000
and he will pay nickel for every ten Herschel smash.

06:16.000 --> 06:17.000
[rat squeaking]

06:17.000 --> 06:18.000
[grunts]

06:19.000 --> 06:22.000
[Herschel] It is not dream job.

06:22.000 --> 06:25.000
But I am grateful for chance to prove my worth.

06:25.000 --> 06:28.000
Get your seltzer water here! Just one bright, shiny nickel.

06:28.000 --> 06:30.000
[Herschel]  Some things still out of reach.

06:30.000 --> 06:32.000
Seltzer water. Get your seltzer water!

06:32.000 --> 06:33.000
Yeah, you, sir. Seltzer water today?

06:34.000 --> 06:36.000
It's only one bright, shiny nickel for the men.

06:36.000 --> 06:38.000
It's only one bright, shiny nickel for the ladies.

06:40.000 --> 06:44.000
[Herschel]  But over time we work and save.

06:45.000 --> 06:47.000
I grant Sarah's wish.

06:47.000 --> 06:51.000
A beautiful Greenbaum family plot

06:51.000 --> 06:53.000
for us to share.

06:53.000 --> 06:54.000
Forever.

06:57.000 --> 07:01.000
Then Hashem gives us biggest miracle of all.

07:03.000 --> 07:05.000
So one night to Sarah

07:05.000 --> 07:07.000
I make this vow.

07:08.000 --> 07:11.000
Our child will be strong.

07:12.000 --> 07:15.000
And our child's child will be strong.

07:16.000 --> 07:19.000
Our family will prosper.

07:20.000 --> 07:23.000
And in 100 years,

07:23.000 --> 07:25.000
the Greenbaums will be powerful.

07:27.000 --> 07:28.000
Successful.

07:28.000 --> 07:31.000
The strongest in the land.

07:36.000 --> 07:38.000
[Herschel] And then one day,

07:39.000 --> 07:41.000
everything changed.

07:41.000 --> 07:42.000
[rats squeaking]

07:51.000 --> 07:52.000
[squeaking]

08:04.000 --> 08:05.000
[screaming]

08:13.000 --> 08:14.000
Attention!

08:14.000 --> 08:18.000
This factory has been condemned.

08:18.000 --> 08:19.000
[indistinct chatter]

08:59.000 --> 09:00.000
[thuds]

09:00.000 --> 09:01.000
-Damn it. -Shit.

09:09.000 --> 09:11.000
[boy 1] Dude, we're never gonna find this, bro.

09:11.000 --> 09:12.000
[boy 2] No, it's definitely this way.

09:20.000 --> 09:21.000
Whoa.

09:27.000 --> 09:29.000
[lid clattering]

09:40.000 --> 09:42.000
[all screaming]

09:42.000 --> 09:43.000
[boy] Let's go!

09:44.000 --> 09:45.000
[breathing heavily]

09:51.000 --> 09:52.000
-[indistinct chatter] -[cameras flashing]

09:55.000 --> 09:58.000
Please! Please! Settle down.

09:58.000 --> 10:02.000
Essentially, the pickle brine preserved him perfectly.

10:02.000 --> 10:06.000
It's been 100 years, but he hasn't aged a day.

10:06.000 --> 10:09.000
-That's impossible. -You don't honestly expect us

10:06.000 --> 10:09.000
to buy that, do you?

10:09.000 --> 10:11.000
What's the science behind it?

10:11.000 --> 10:13.000
Please, let me explain.

10:13.000 --> 10:15.000
[Herschel] The scientist explains.

10:15.000 --> 10:17.000
His logic is good.

10:18.000 --> 10:20.000
It satisfies everyone.

10:20.000 --> 10:21.000
-Oh, yes. -It makes sense.

10:21.000 --> 10:22.000
-Absolutely. -Very clear.

10:23.000 --> 10:24.000
[Herschel]  But...

10:24.000 --> 10:26.000
I'm very sad.

10:26.000 --> 10:29.000
The world has changed.

10:29.000 --> 10:32.000
Everything I know is gone. And...

10:33.000 --> 10:35.000
...everyone.

10:35.000 --> 10:37.000
[doctor] I'm so sorry, Herschel.

10:39.000 --> 10:41.000
You will check again.

10:41.000 --> 10:43.000
We already checked the city records twice.

10:44.000 --> 10:46.000
She wasn't brined.

10:46.000 --> 10:48.000
She's been dead for 80 years.

10:48.000 --> 10:49.000
You will check again.

10:49.000 --> 10:50.000
We already checked.

10:51.000 --> 10:52.000
[grunts]

10:54.000 --> 10:55.000
[alarm beeping]

10:55.000 --> 10:57.000
[Herschel] My Sarah is gone.

10:57.000 --> 10:59.000
Our child is gone.

11:00.000 --> 11:02.000
I have nothing.

11:03.000 --> 11:07.000
Then I get some great news.

11:07.000 --> 11:08.000
Great news, Herschel.

11:09.000 --> 11:10.000
It took a little bit of doing,

11:10.000 --> 11:13.000
but we were able to track down a living relative.

11:13.000 --> 11:15.000
I have family?

11:15.000 --> 11:16.000
Yes.

11:16.000 --> 11:18.000
A great-grandson.

11:18.000 --> 11:21.000
And, as luck would have it, he lives right here in Brooklyn

11:21.000 --> 11:24.000
and he's exactly the same age as you.

11:24.000 --> 11:27.000
-His name is "Ben Greenbaum." -[sighs]

11:27.000 --> 11:30.000
And we're contacting him right now.

11:30.000 --> 11:31.000
Thank you.

11:34.000 --> 11:37.000
[Herschel]  I am so excited I forget all my misery.

11:38.000 --> 11:40.000
Even though I have not met this Ben,

11:40.000 --> 11:43.000
I can see him in my mind.

11:44.000 --> 11:47.000
He will be just like how I vowed to Sarah,

11:48.000 --> 11:49.000
powerful.

11:49.000 --> 11:50.000
Successful.

11:51.000 --> 11:53.000
The strongest in the land.

11:57.000 --> 11:59.000
[man speaking indistinctly]

12:00.000 --> 12:03.000
[man sneezes four times]

12:03.000 --> 12:04.000
-[woman] Bless you. -[man] Oh, I'm sorry.

12:04.000 --> 12:06.000
Excuse me.

12:08.000 --> 12:09.000
Greenbaum.

12:14.000 --> 12:15.000
Yeah.

12:18.000 --> 12:19.000
Greenbaum.

12:22.000 --> 12:23.000
Greenbaum.

12:24.000 --> 12:25.000
Greenbaum.

12:26.000 --> 12:27.000
Greenbaum!

12:27.000 --> 12:29.000
Greenbaum!

12:29.000 --> 12:30.000
Greenbaum!

12:30.000 --> 12:31.000
[laughs]

12:32.000 --> 12:33.000
All right!

12:34.000 --> 12:36.000
This is nuts. [laughs]

12:37.000 --> 12:39.000
It must be so crazy for you.

12:40.000 --> 12:41.000
Very crazy.

12:41.000 --> 12:43.000
Crazy for me, too, man.

12:44.000 --> 12:45.000
Are you allowed to leave?

12:45.000 --> 12:47.000
Do you wanna come back to my apartment?

12:47.000 --> 12:50.000
-Very much. -All right. Let's go.

12:54.000 --> 12:57.000
[Ben] Yeah, I got him. I'm his great-grandson.

12:57.000 --> 13:00.000
So he's gonna stay with me for a bit. Yeah. Thank you.

13:00.000 --> 13:02.000
[car honking]

13:06.000 --> 13:08.000
[Ben] Take it in.

13:18.000 --> 13:19.000
Cool, huh?

13:21.000 --> 13:22.000
Make way.

13:23.000 --> 13:25.000
[Ben] It's a scooter.

13:25.000 --> 13:27.000
They're actually pretty fun.

13:27.000 --> 13:30.000
Anyway, I can't wait to show you, like, the future.

13:30.000 --> 13:33.000
There's so much cool shit, man. You're gonna love it.

13:35.000 --> 13:36.000
[horn honking]

13:39.000 --> 13:40.000
It's cool, man. It's a cab.

13:40.000 --> 13:43.000
It's gonna take us back to my apartment. Hop in.

13:49.000 --> 13:51.000
[chuckles] It's all right.

13:53.000 --> 13:54.000
Oh, yeah, crawl in.

13:54.000 --> 13:56.000
There you go. You got it.

13:57.000 --> 13:59.000
We're going to Brooklyn, please. Thank you.

14:08.000 --> 14:09.000
Here we are, man.

14:09.000 --> 14:11.000
Home, sweet home.

14:11.000 --> 14:12.000
Hey, check this out.

14:12.000 --> 14:14.000
Alexa, lights.

14:14.000 --> 14:16.000
Pretty cool, huh?

14:16.000 --> 14:18.000
All this yours?

14:18.000 --> 14:20.000
Yeah. I mean, I don't own it or anything like that.

14:20.000 --> 14:23.000
I do live here by myself. I work from home,

14:20.000 --> 14:23.000
though, a lot.

14:23.000 --> 14:25.000
It would be nice, honestly, to have someone around.

14:25.000 --> 14:27.000
So you can stay here as long as you want.

14:27.000 --> 14:30.000
I do not want to be burden to you.

14:30.000 --> 14:33.000
It's not a burden, Herschel. At all. I mean...

14:34.000 --> 14:36.000
I'm amazed you're alive. [chuckles]

14:38.000 --> 14:40.000
I really never thought I would get a chance

14:40.000 --> 14:42.000
to meet another Greenbaum. So...

14:43.000 --> 14:45.000
Neither did I.

14:47.000 --> 14:48.000
You must be thirsty.

14:48.000 --> 14:51.000
I mean, you were brined for, like, a century.

14:51.000 --> 14:53.000
And there's salt in brine, right?

14:53.000 --> 14:55.000
So you must be pretty parched, to say the least.

14:56.000 --> 14:58.000
Can I get you something to drink?

14:58.000 --> 15:01.000
Macadamia milk? Or there's cashew milk.

15:01.000 --> 15:04.000
I got pea milk. They're milking peas now.

15:04.000 --> 15:06.000
They're milking everything these days, dude.

15:06.000 --> 15:08.000
You name it, they're milking it.

15:08.000 --> 15:11.000
I got mint tea. I have kombucha.

15:12.000 --> 15:14.000
-"Kombucha"? -Yeah.

15:14.000 --> 15:18.000
It's fermented... stuff. Honestly, I don't even know.

15:18.000 --> 15:20.000
Tastes nasty. But it's very healthy.

15:20.000 --> 15:22.000
-Would you like some? -Is fine.

15:22.000 --> 15:26.000
They inject drink into my arm in hospital.

15:26.000 --> 15:29.000
-I am fine. -Fair enough.

15:29.000 --> 15:31.000
There must be something I can get you.

15:31.000 --> 15:33.000
Would you like some seltzer?

15:35.000 --> 15:38.000
You have seltzer.

15:38.000 --> 15:40.000
Oh, I got seltzer for days, son.

15:40.000 --> 15:44.000
I got a whole seltzer machine. It's pretty cool, actually.

15:44.000 --> 15:47.000
Ya just fill this up there.

15:48.000 --> 15:51.000
That's it. You put in the cartridge.

15:51.000 --> 15:52.000
"Cartridge."

15:52.000 --> 15:55.000
And you just press that button. Makes you seltzer.

15:56.000 --> 15:57.000
Press button.

15:57.000 --> 15:59.000
Exactly. You wanna press it?

16:01.000 --> 16:03.000
You'll let me press seltzer button?

16:03.000 --> 16:06.000
Yeah. It's a pretty big deal, but we're family.

16:06.000 --> 16:08.000
So you can press the seltzer button.

16:08.000 --> 16:09.000
Knock yourself out.

16:12.000 --> 16:14.000
Yeah!

16:15.000 --> 16:17.000
There you go. You're seltzering.

16:17.000 --> 16:19.000
Pretty cool, huh?

16:19.000 --> 16:21.000
-The bubble. -So many bubbles.

16:21.000 --> 16:22.000
Well...

16:23.000 --> 16:27.000
One for you. And one for me.

16:33.000 --> 16:34.000
Cheers.

16:36.000 --> 16:37.000
L'chaim.

16:40.000 --> 16:41.000
Ooh!

16:41.000 --> 16:43.000
[chuckles]

16:45.000 --> 16:47.000
Yeah.

16:47.000 --> 16:49.000
Lots of bubbles. [chuckles]

16:50.000 --> 16:51.000
Crazy.

16:51.000 --> 16:53.000
This must be very overwhelming for you.

16:53.000 --> 16:54.000
It's a lot. It's a little much.

16:54.000 --> 16:56.000
But I think you'll find there's actually, like,

16:56.000 --> 16:58.000
some pretty cool stuff about the future.

16:58.000 --> 16:59.000
[scoffing]

16:59.000 --> 17:01.000
Oh, yeah. Exactly. Not just that.

17:01.000 --> 17:04.000
Uh, I know what else you might like.

17:04.000 --> 17:06.000
You like music, right?

17:06.000 --> 17:07.000
Yes.

17:07.000 --> 17:08.000
Watch this.

17:08.000 --> 17:09.000
Alexa, play...

17:10.000 --> 17:11.000
oldies.

17:12.000 --> 17:14.000
[Alexa]  Here's a station for you. Oldies.

17:14.000 --> 17:15.000
["Stay" playing]

