20:55.000 --> 20:58.000
I guess, these days

20:58.000 --> 21:01.000
to give apps, like, silly names.

21:01.000 --> 21:04.000
You know, Venmo, Hulu, Hipmunk and...

21:07.000 --> 21:09.000
You know, you might think it's kinda silly.

21:09.000 --> 21:10.000
But I've been working on it pretty hard

21:11.000 --> 21:14.000
for five years now, basically.

21:14.000 --> 21:16.000
And once I sell this thing, I can finally, you know,

21:16.000 --> 21:19.000
start the next chapter, which is exciting.

21:19.000 --> 21:22.000
You work for five years. How come you no sell?

21:22.000 --> 21:24.000
It's just...

21:24.000 --> 21:26.000
not ready yet.

21:26.000 --> 21:28.000
I'm still finalizing some things.

21:28.000 --> 21:32.000
Just really focused on getting it right, you know?

21:28.000 --> 21:32.000
Making it perfect.

21:32.000 --> 21:36.000
I think once it's ready, though, I'll have

21:32.000 --> 21:36.000
a pretty easy time selling it.

21:36.000 --> 21:39.000
I went to school with this guy who works in venture capital.

21:39.000 --> 21:41.000
And I'm pretty sure he'd be into it.

21:41.000 --> 21:43.000
He said that they wanna hear the pitch as soon as it's done.

21:43.000 --> 21:45.000
But I'm still kind of noodling with the logo.

21:45.000 --> 21:48.000
I mean, this mustardy one has really been growing on me.

21:48.000 --> 21:50.000
I kinda wish it was mustardier, though.

21:51.000 --> 21:53.000
Is this your father?

21:53.000 --> 21:54.000
No, that's David Bowie.

21:55.000 --> 21:56.000
Is this your mother?

21:56.000 --> 21:58.000
No, that's also David Bowie.

21:58.000 --> 22:00.000
That whole poster's David Bowie.

22:05.000 --> 22:08.000
How come in this whole place you have so many things,

22:08.000 --> 22:10.000
but no pictures of family?

22:10.000 --> 22:12.000
I have pictures of my family.

22:12.000 --> 22:15.000
I just haven't really,

22:15.000 --> 22:18.000
you know, like, framed them and incorporated them in my...

22:19.000 --> 22:21.000
design.

22:21.000 --> 22:23.000
But I got that stuff right here.

22:38.000 --> 22:39.000
[sighs]

22:49.000 --> 22:50.000
You kept.

22:50.000 --> 22:53.000
Yeah. I kept.

22:58.000 --> 22:59.000
[exhales heavily]

23:09.000 --> 23:10.000
Who is this?

23:11.000 --> 23:12.000
That's...

23:13.000 --> 23:14.000
your son.

23:14.000 --> 23:17.000
It's Mort Greenbaum.

23:20.000 --> 23:21.000
"Mort"?

23:25.000 --> 23:26.000
[sighs]

23:26.000 --> 23:28.000
Sarah had son.

23:36.000 --> 23:38.000
How was his life?

23:38.000 --> 23:40.000
Was he success?

23:40.000 --> 23:44.000
Yeah. He was a foreman of a brick factory.

23:45.000 --> 23:46.000
A foreman?

23:47.000 --> 23:48.000
Yeah.

23:52.000 --> 23:53.000
Who is this?

23:53.000 --> 23:54.000
Uh...

23:56.000 --> 23:58.000
That's Mort's son.

23:58.000 --> 24:01.000
David Greenbaum. Your grandson.

24:02.000 --> 24:04.000
He was also foreman?

24:04.000 --> 24:06.000
He was an accountant.

24:06.000 --> 24:08.000
-Accountant. -Yeah.

24:09.000 --> 24:10.000
This his wife?

24:10.000 --> 24:11.000
Mm-hmm.

24:14.000 --> 24:18.000
Who is this very shapely young woman here?

24:19.000 --> 24:20.000
That's me.

24:27.000 --> 24:29.000
These are your parents.

24:31.000 --> 24:32.000
Where are they?

24:34.000 --> 24:35.000
They passed away.

24:37.000 --> 24:39.000
I'm very sorry.

24:39.000 --> 24:40.000
Murdered or regular?

24:41.000 --> 24:42.000
It was a car crash.

24:42.000 --> 24:44.000
So, regular.

24:44.000 --> 24:46.000
You will tell me everything of their death

24:46.000 --> 24:49.000
so I may bear witness to your grief.

24:49.000 --> 24:53.000
How their bodies died, their faces as the life left.

24:53.000 --> 24:54.000
Be very specific.

24:54.000 --> 24:56.000
Spare no detail.

24:56.000 --> 24:58.000
We will bond over our pain.

24:58.000 --> 24:59.000
No detail too small.

24:59.000 --> 25:01.000
We don't have to get into that right now.

25:01.000 --> 25:03.000
You wanna get outta here? Let's go to Smorgasburg.

25:03.000 --> 25:06.000
They have jackfruit nachos that are actually really good.

25:07.000 --> 25:08.000
We will go to cemetery now.

25:08.000 --> 25:10.000
Visit Greenbaum family grave, pay our respect to dead.

25:10.000 --> 25:12.000
Actually, I'm not sure...

25:12.000 --> 25:14.000
I don't think the cemetery's open right now.

25:14.000 --> 25:16.000
So we go to cemetery tomorrow.

25:16.000 --> 25:18.000
I think it was maybe supposed to rain.

25:18.000 --> 25:20.000
So I guess weather permitting.

25:20.000 --> 25:22.000
All right. But now we go to shul,

25:22.000 --> 25:24.000
we say Mourner's Kaddish, prayer for dead.

25:24.000 --> 25:30.000
Must properly honor memory of Sarah, Mort, your parents.

25:31.000 --> 25:33.000
Yeah, I'm not...

25:33.000 --> 25:35.000
I'm not sure that's something I want to do right now.

25:35.000 --> 25:39.000
But I would be happy to walk you over there.

25:39.000 --> 25:41.000
What is problem?

25:41.000 --> 25:42.000
It's not a problem.

25:42.000 --> 25:47.000
I guess I understand why you're a religious person.

25:47.000 --> 25:50.000
That makes sense for someone from your era.

25:50.000 --> 25:53.000
But I am not...

25:53.000 --> 25:54.000
I'm not very religious.

25:54.000 --> 25:56.000
You do not know Mourner's Kaddish?

25:58.000 --> 25:59.000
[clicks tongue]

25:59.000 --> 26:01.000
Not anymore, no.

26:02.000 --> 26:04.000
How do you grieve for dead parents

26:04.000 --> 26:06.000
if you do not say prayer for dead?

26:06.000 --> 26:08.000
I'm doing okay.

26:11.000 --> 26:13.000
I do not understand.

26:15.000 --> 26:16.000
You were raised Jew.

26:17.000 --> 26:17.000
Yeah.

26:17.000 --> 26:20.000
Are you not still Jew?

26:20.000 --> 26:22.000
Technically.

26:22.000 --> 26:24.000
I also had a Jumanji-themed bar mitzvah.

26:24.000 --> 26:27.000
It's not like I was that religious

26:24.000 --> 26:27.000
in the first place.

26:27.000 --> 26:30.000
Also, like, organized religion is very regressive.

27:04.000 --> 27:05.000
[sighs]

27:09.000 --> 27:13.000
Praise Hashem, there is still beautiful Greenbaum plot.

27:13.000 --> 27:16.000
Very special place. Very special.

27:16.000 --> 27:19.000
Tell me, how high is elm tree now?

27:19.000 --> 27:20.000
100 feet?

27:20.000 --> 27:22.000
200 feet?

27:22.000 --> 27:26.000
Yeah. Something like that. Probably. I'm not 100% sure.

27:26.000 --> 27:28.000
When last time you come?

27:28.000 --> 27:32.000
I don't know, maybe like five years ago, or somethin'.

27:32.000 --> 27:34.000
So been a little while.

27:35.000 --> 27:36.000
Wait.

27:37.000 --> 27:38.000
It's this way.

27:39.000 --> 27:40.000
This way!

27:55.000 --> 27:57.000
Sweet Hashem.

28:07.000 --> 28:08.000
You let them put garbage.

28:10.000 --> 28:14.000
And you let them put huge sign block out sun and kill tree!

28:14.000 --> 28:16.000
Yeah, it's not on our property.

28:16.000 --> 28:17.000
There's nothing we can do about it.

28:25.000 --> 28:26.000
Sarah.

28:41.000 --> 28:42.000
[Herschel sniffles]

28:42.000 --> 28:43.000
You okay?

28:49.000 --> 28:51.000
We will pray.

28:52.000 --> 28:54.000
[praying in foreign language]

29:18.000 --> 29:19.000
Hey, guys!

29:20.000 --> 29:22.000
Sorry, you can't be there.

29:23.000 --> 29:24.000
What?

29:24.000 --> 29:26.000
We're putting up a billboard!

29:33.000 --> 29:34.000
[Herschel] What it say?

29:35.000 --> 29:37.000
It's an ad for vanilla-flavored vodka.

29:39.000 --> 29:41.000
Vanilla-flavored...

29:43.000 --> 29:44.000
...vodka?

29:48.000 --> 29:49.000
Cossacks.

29:51.000 --> 29:52.000
Cossack!

29:54.000 --> 29:56.000
Hershel, what are you doin', man?

29:58.000 --> 30:01.000
You will take down vanilla vodka...

30:02.000 --> 30:03.000
or I will do violence.

30:04.000 --> 30:05.000
What?

30:05.000 --> 30:10.000
You will take down vanilla vodka...

30:13.000 --> 30:14.000
or I will do violence.

30:14.000 --> 30:16.000
Look, buddy, I don't have time for--

30:17.000 --> 30:19.000
Oh, shit. No!

30:19.000 --> 30:20.000
[grunting]

30:26.000 --> 30:28.000
-Stop! -Yes!

30:32.000 --> 30:33.000
Stop!

30:35.000 --> 30:37.000
Come on! Come on!

30:37.000 --> 30:39.000
Ben! Ben!

30:39.000 --> 30:40.000
Come on!

30:40.000 --> 30:42.000
You can never stop the Greenbaums!

30:42.000 --> 30:44.000
You will never stop the Greenbaums!

30:46.000 --> 30:48.000
[door buzzes]

30:48.000 --> 30:51.000
Your payment's been processed. You're free to go.

30:52.000 --> 30:54.000
Fantastic.

30:55.000 --> 30:57.000
We must go back to grave.

30:57.000 --> 31:00.000
We will cut down Cossack billboard.

31:01.000 --> 31:02.000
Dude, if we do that,

31:02.000 --> 31:04.000
we're gonna go back to jail. So, no.

31:04.000 --> 31:08.000
Okay. We must purchase billboard from Cossack,

31:04.000 --> 31:08.000
which I do not like,

31:08.000 --> 31:10.000
and then we cut down billboard.

31:10.000 --> 31:12.000
First off, the Cossacks don't own it.

31:12.000 --> 31:15.000
Second off, it's owned by some giant billboard company.

31:12.000 --> 31:15.000
It costs $200,000.

31:15.000 --> 31:19.000
Then we buy from giant company and then we cut down billboard.

31:19.000 --> 31:21.000
Why are you being so difficult about this?

31:21.000 --> 31:22.000
I can't afford it!

31:22.000 --> 31:24.000
You have moneys? Your parents leave you moneys?

31:24.000 --> 31:25.000
I don't have $200,000.

31:25.000 --> 31:27.000
You have all this, so you have moneys.

31:27.000 --> 31:29.000
How much moneys you have?

31:29.000 --> 31:31.000
I have some money left, but I don't have a lot left.

31:31.000 --> 31:33.000
And I have a lot less now that I had to bail us

31:31.000 --> 31:33.000
out of jail, Herschel.

31:33.000 --> 31:35.000
It's not my fault!

31:35.000 --> 31:37.000
What is your fault is that you started a fight with

31:35.000 --> 31:37.000
some construction workers!

31:37.000 --> 31:40.000
Someone has to defend honor of family. Not you.

31:40.000 --> 31:42.000
And I'd be defending the honor of our family more

31:42.000 --> 31:46.000
if I wasn't busy trying to create a company

31:42.000 --> 31:46.000
and a product, man!

31:46.000 --> 31:49.000
You're busy? Oh, yes. Not selling Boop Bops.

31:49.000 --> 31:52.000
You don't understand how much pressure there is

31:49.000 --> 31:52.000
on this stuff. Okay?

31:52.000 --> 31:53.000
I'm trying to make it perfect.

31:54.000 --> 31:56.000
Blue. Green. Red. Who cares?

31:56.000 --> 31:58.000
Pick a color!

31:58.000 --> 32:00.000
Companies are made or broken by the color of their logo!

32:00.000 --> 32:02.000
Let me tell you something.

32:02.000 --> 32:04.000
In Schlupsk, we have saying.

32:04.000 --> 32:06.000
Oh, good. Yeah, what is it? I'm sure this has aged well.

32:06.000 --> 32:09.000
If man says he is going to throw punch,

32:09.000 --> 32:11.000
but he does not throw punch,

32:11.000 --> 32:14.000
it is because this man secretly has polio arm.

32:16.000 --> 32:17.000
This is you.

32:17.000 --> 32:19.000
You have polio arm.

32:19.000 --> 32:21.000
This your polio arm.

32:21.000 --> 32:22.000
Throw your punch!

32:22.000 --> 32:24.000
Do something, Ben!

32:24.000 --> 32:26.000
Don't just sit there, looking at Boop Bops.

32:26.000 --> 32:28.000
Blue, yellow, green! Who cares?

32:29.000 --> 32:30.000
Throw your punch!

32:30.000 --> 32:33.000
Okay. Fine! You know what? Fine! Fine!

32:33.000 --> 32:35.000
-Good. Good. Do it. -I'll email the guy.

32:35.000 --> 32:37.000
No choice anyway. I have no money.

32:37.000 --> 32:40.000
It's not ready. Logo's not right.

32:40.000 --> 32:43.000
Who cares about the stupid logo?

32:43.000 --> 32:44.000
[message alert chimes]

32:44.000 --> 32:46.000
You know they cured polio, right?

32:46.000 --> 32:47.000
-They did? -Yes, they did.

32:47.000 --> 32:50.000
A long time ago. A guy named Jonas Salk.

32:50.000 --> 32:51.000
Was he Jew?

32:51.000 --> 32:52.000
He was. Yes.

32:52.000 --> 32:53.000
-He was Jewish? -Yes.

32:53.000 --> 32:55.000
Yes! Knew it.

32:55.000 --> 32:56.000
Oh, yeah, big win.

32:56.000 --> 32:59.000
I would look at polio people and think,

32:59.000 --> 33:00.000
"They could fix this."

33:00.000 --> 33:01.000
You thought that?

33:01.000 --> 33:04.000
This problem not unfixable problem.

33:04.000 --> 33:06.000
You put a Jew on this, he will fix this.

33:07.000 --> 33:08.000
Very prophetic of you, Herschel.

33:08.000 --> 33:09.000
I was right. Very good.

33:10.000 --> 33:11.000
[message alert chimes]

33:13.000 --> 33:15.000
He's texting back.

33:15.000 --> 33:17.000
He says my idea's "straight fire."

33:17.000 --> 33:18.000
That's a good thing.

33:19.000 --> 33:22.000
He wants me to come in today and pitch my idea in person.

33:22.000 --> 33:23.000
He wants your Boop Bops.

33:23.000 --> 33:25.000
-This is a big deal, Herschel. -Yes.

33:27.000 --> 33:28.000
He wants my Boop Bops.

33:31.000 --> 33:32.000
Ben, what's up?

33:33.000 --> 33:34.000
Hey! How's it going, man?

33:35.000 --> 33:37.000
We're not gonna invest.

33:39.000 --> 33:41.000
-What? -Yeah. Sorry, man.

33:42.000 --> 33:43.000
What's the problem?

33:43.000 --> 33:44.000
Before you came in, we googled your name

33:45.000 --> 33:47.000
and the first thing that comes up is your arrest.

33:48.000 --> 33:49.000
Look, it's just bad optics.

33:49.000 --> 33:52.000
I mean, the whole app is about ethics,

33:52.000 --> 33:54.000
and the founder is a violent criminal.

33:54.000 --> 33:56.000
Like, if you Boop Bopped Boop Bop,

33:56.000 --> 33:59.000
you'd get a really low Boop Bop score.

33:59.000 --> 34:00.000
Is there anything we can do?

34:00.000 --> 34:02.000
Can we spin this or something like that?

34:02.000 --> 34:03.000
Oh, no. Definitely not.

34:03.000 --> 34:06.000
No one's gonna touch this, man. This is...

34:06.000 --> 34:07.000
This idea is dead.

34:07.000 --> 34:08.000
[sighs]

34:08.000 --> 34:10.000
Look, consider this an opportunity.

34:10.000 --> 34:11.000
I mean, there's tons of other ideas.

34:11.000 --> 34:14.000
-How long did it take to come up with this?

34:11.000 --> 34:14.000
-Five years.

34:14.000 --> 34:16.000
Five years. That's--

34:16.000 --> 34:17.000
Long time.

34:17.000 --> 34:18.000
Yeah, that's a while.

34:18.000 --> 34:20.000
Sorry to disappoint you, I guess.

34:20.000 --> 34:24.000
Maybe you can make an app where it doesn't matter

34:20.000 --> 34:24.000
if the founder's a bad person.

34:24.000 --> 34:26.000
Like a social media thing.

34:26.000 --> 34:30.000
Hey. I don't know if you want my advice, man,

34:30.000 --> 34:34.000
but it's never too late to do things completely differently.

34:30.000 --> 34:34.000
You know?

34:34.000 --> 34:35.000
-Yeah. -Yeah.

34:36.000 --> 34:37.000
Take care, man.

34:37.000 --> 34:39.000
Call me if you got anything new.

34:50.000 --> 34:51.000
[door opening]

34:55.000 --> 34:57.000
Did you get moneys?

34:57.000 --> 34:59.000
No. I didn't get moneys.

34:59.000 --> 35:02.000
And I'm afraid that I might never get moneys

35:02.000 --> 35:06.000
for my business that is based on ethics

35:06.000 --> 35:11.000
now that I have a criminal record for assault

35:06.000 --> 35:11.000
because of you!

35:14.000 --> 35:16.000
I was worried no one would want your Boop Bops

35:16.000 --> 35:19.000
because is terrible idea. So...

35:19.000 --> 35:21.000
I have other idea.

35:21.000 --> 35:24.000
We start pickle business.

35:24.000 --> 35:26.000
Is good business. Jewish business.

35:26.000 --> 35:28.000
I have knowledge of pickling.

35:28.000 --> 35:31.000
I was myself a pickle.

35:31.000 --> 35:33.000
That's a very stupid idea, Herschel.

35:34.000 --> 35:35.000
It will work.

35:35.000 --> 35:37.000
We will start pickle business.

35:38.000 --> 35:39.000
We will become success.

35:39.000 --> 35:42.000
You will finally make dead parents proud.

35:42.000 --> 35:44.000
Don't you talk about my parents.

35:44.000 --> 35:45.000
You never talk about my parents!

35:46.000 --> 35:49.000
You don't know anything about them!

35:46.000 --> 35:49.000
You never met them!

35:49.000 --> 35:53.000
'Cause you were too busy getting pickle-brined

35:49.000 --> 35:53.000
for 100 years!

35:53.000 --> 35:55.000
It's your fault, Herschel.

35:55.000 --> 35:56.000
You got us arrested.

35:56.000 --> 36:00.000
You ruined my business that I spent years on!

36:03.000 --> 36:04.000
It's a good thing Sarah's not around anymore.

36:05.000 --> 36:07.000
'Cause if she was, she would be ashamed of you.

36:07.000 --> 36:09.000
[dramatic music playing]

36:13.000 --> 36:15.000
You hear this vow.

36:16.000 --> 36:19.000
I will create pickle empire.

36:19.000 --> 36:22.000
I will make $200,000.

36:22.000 --> 36:24.000
I will buy back Cossack land.

36:24.000 --> 36:27.000
And I will cut down billboard.

36:27.000 --> 36:30.000
I will prove you stupid.

36:30.000 --> 36:32.000
Because you are my enemy.

36:33.000 --> 36:36.000
You dishonor Greenbaum name.

36:36.000 --> 36:39.000
We are no longer family.

36:39.000 --> 36:40.000
[Ben] Good luck with that.

36:40.000 --> 36:42.000
You don't know jack shit about shit, man.

36:42.000 --> 36:44.000
You can't even read from what I can tell.

36:44.000 --> 36:45.000
You're gonna start a pickle empire?

36:45.000 --> 36:47.000
You can't even survive out there without my help!

36:47.000 --> 36:50.000
Do not need help from anybody.

36:50.000 --> 36:55.000
I will prove you stupid with no help from anybody ever!

37:22.000 --> 37:24.000
I would like to purchase. How much?

37:26.000 --> 37:29.000
Looks like these are 90 cents apiece.

37:29.000 --> 37:31.000
Terribly sorry, little boy. It sounds to me

37:31.000 --> 37:36.000
like you are saying these cucumbers

37:31.000 --> 37:36.000
are 90 cents apiece.

37:36.000 --> 37:37.000
I am.

37:58.000 --> 37:59.000
Cucumber.

38:01.000 --> 38:02.000
And salt.

38:04.000 --> 38:06.000
Yes!

38:09.000 --> 38:10.000
[upbeat music playing]

38:45.000 --> 38:46.000
[thunder rumbling]

38:55.000 --> 38:57.000
Yes!

39:03.000 --> 39:04.000
[horn honking]

39:17.000 --> 39:18.000
[man] Oh, my God. Kevin, look.

39:18.000 --> 39:20.000
Artisanal pickles.

39:21.000 --> 39:22.000
Well, he's not on Yelp.

39:22.000 --> 39:27.000
Sir. How local is your produce?

39:27.000 --> 39:29.000
I make pickle here in Brooklyn.

39:29.000 --> 39:30.000
And are they all-natural?

39:31.000 --> 39:32.000
Is pickle.

39:32.000 --> 39:34.000
But do you add any chemicals like,

39:34.000 --> 39:36.000
you know, benzoates or preservatives?

39:38.000 --> 39:40.000
I do not even know these words.

39:40.000 --> 39:42.000
Oh, I like your style.

39:42.000 --> 39:43.000
Ooh, let's see.

39:43.000 --> 39:45.000
Wow! Ooh.

39:45.000 --> 39:47.000
Just hits me in my throat.

39:47.000 --> 39:48.000
Very pungent.

39:48.000 --> 39:49.000
Let me smell it.

39:49.000 --> 39:51.000
Oh! Yeah, that burns.

39:51.000 --> 39:52.000
You can feel the burn.

39:52.000 --> 39:54.000
I can, like, smell it in my eye.

39:54.000 --> 39:55.000
Feel the sting.

39:55.000 --> 39:57.000
Give it to me again. Let me smell it.

39:57.000 --> 39:59.000
Mm, yeah, that's straight from the devil.

40:00.000 --> 40:01.000
Satanic. Oh, it stinks.

40:01.000 --> 40:04.000
You know what, it would go so good

